<li>High-stitch designs: Per-stitch protects earnings on large counts.</li>
<li>Low-stitch, high-complexity: A flat rate or hourly avoids undercharging=
.</li>
<li>Specialty materials: Add surcharges for fabrics or threads that demand =
extra care.</li>
</ul>
<p>Example hybrid: 20,000 stitches at $2/1,000 =3D $40, plus 1 hour setup a=
t $30/hour, plus materials and markup.</p>
